# Hugo layouts and templates

Site overrides live in root `layouts/`, `assets/`, and `static/` — prefer these over editing `themes/hugo-theme-bootstrap/`. If you must touch the vendored theme, keep the diff minimal.

## After template or asset changes

Run a local Hugo build so failures surface before push:

```bash
hugo server -D          # iteration
hugo --minify --environment production   # production parity
```

Or Docker Compose / commands in `README.md` (Hugo version from `.env`). Pull requests also run the production Docker build via `.github/workflows/hugo-build.yml`.

## SEO partials

- Document `<title>`: `layouts/partials/head/title.html` (home falls back to `Site.Title`).
- List/archive meta descriptions: `layouts/partials/head/list-page-description.html` (short per-page copy, ≤160 characters; pagination suffix on page 2+).
- Paginated list `noindex`: `layouts/partials/head/meta/robots.html` + `params.listPaginationMetaRobots` in `config/_default/config.toml`.
- Open Graph, Twitter, JSON-LD: follow existing patterns in `layouts/partials/head.html` and related partials.
- New external hosts, share imagery, or scripts must stay coherent with CSP, response headers, and `staticwebapp.config.json`.

## Images in templates

HTML partials and shortcodes that emit `<img>` need appropriate `alt` (or equivalent ARIA).
